National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and Austrian Chancellor Sebastian Kurz held a phone call to discuss the strong U.S.-Austria relationship and the restoration of transatlantic ties. They agreed to collaborate on various global challenges, such as climate change, economic recovery from the COVID-19 pandemic, and counterterrorism. The two leaders also talked about coordinating efforts on shared foreign policy priorities, including the Western Balkans and China. Additionally, they explored opportunities to safeguard religious freedom worldwide.